176
00:15:05.195 --> 00:15:07.781 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I wonder if it's from back then.</i>

177
00:15:08.574 --> 00:15:12.411 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Maybe Izumi-kun hasn't really</i>
<i>come back since he left on that trip.</i>

178
00:15:14.038 --> 00:15:19.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Izumi-kun, remember when your dad
got injured while on a trip and…

179
00:15:22.296 --> 00:15:23.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's go.

180
00:15:25.925 --> 00:15:29.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I guess I shouldn't have</i>
<i>asked him about it.</i>

181
00:15:37.603 --> 00:15:39.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh. So cute!

182
00:15:40.189 --> 00:15:41.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come here!

183
00:15:48.906 --> 00:15:50.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That must be his mom.

184
00:15:50.491 --> 00:15:51.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Must be.

185
00:15:51.450 --> 00:15:53.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are they strays?

186
00:15:53.702 --> 00:15:55.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I guess not.

187
00:15:55.204 --> 00:15:56.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She's wearing a collar.

188
00:15:59.625 --> 00:16:01.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, Izumi-kun?

189
00:16:02.920 --> 00:16:04.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a nice day.

190
00:16:04.755 --> 00:16:06.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not even that cold.

191
00:16:06.882 --> 00:16:09.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're talking like an old man, Izumi-kun.

192
00:16:09.176 --> 00:16:11.011 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, that was mean.

193
00:16:11.095 --> 00:16:13.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mommy!

194
00:16:13.514 --> 00:16:15.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, Mommy!

195
00:16:15.432 --> 00:16:17.351 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait for me!

196
00:16:18.185 --> 00:16:19.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on. Let's go.

197
00:16:22.189 --> 00:16:23.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hurry up, now.

198
00:16:26.193 --> 00:16:29.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stupid Mommy!

199
00:16:29.655 --> 00:16:31.573 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why…

200
00:16:31.657 --> 00:16:33.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why would you say that?

201
00:16:34.034 --> 00:16:36.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hate you, Mommy!

202
00:16:37.204 --> 00:16:38.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, it's not like…

203
00:16:38.956 --> 00:16:40.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not like I…

204
00:16:42.543 --> 00:16:45.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hope you die!

205
00:16:53.429 --> 00:16:55.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on. Let's go.

206
00:16:58.600 --> 00:16:59.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Izumi-kun?

207
00:17:00.352 --> 00:17:01.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A hole.

208
00:17:01.895 --> 00:17:03.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There's a hole.

209
00:17:04.481 --> 00:17:05.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A hole?

210
00:17:06.859 --> 00:17:07.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's wrong?

211
00:17:08.068 --> 00:17:09.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you okay?

212
00:17:09.987 --> 00:17:12.781 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I had a hard time breathing
all of a sudden.

213
00:17:13.824 --> 00:17:15.617 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe I'm just getting old.

214
00:17:15.701 --> 00:17:19.663 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, come on.
You're really acting like an old man now.

215
00:17:22.291 --> 00:17:26.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Sometimes, I feel as though</i>
<i>my body's being ripped apart.</i>

216
00:17:27.629 --> 00:17:29.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But that feeling goes away after a while.</i>

217
00:17:31.258 --> 00:17:36.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That's when I feel as though some part</i>
<i>of Migi's become a part of my heart.</i>

218
00:17:38.057 --> 00:17:40.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But I still do like her.</i>

219
00:17:42.186 --> 00:17:43.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I really care about her.</i>

220
00:17:45.230 --> 00:17:49.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>That feeling is mine alone.</i>

221
00:17:51.487 --> 00:17:53.989 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>When things are going well</i>
<i>with me and her,</i>

222
00:17:54.823 --> 00:17:57.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I always wish you would stay asleep,</i>

223
00:17:59.244 --> 00:18:00.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Migi.</i>

224
00:18:22.351 --> 00:18:23.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
See you later.

225
00:18:23.477 --> 00:18:24.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Okay.

226
00:18:31.944 --> 00:18:35.322 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>You're Izumi Shinichi-kun, right?</i>

227
00:18:41.453 --> 00:18:42.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>If only…</i>

228
00:18:45.541 --> 00:18:48.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>If only we'd gotten closer much sooner.</i>

229
00:18:50.170 --> 00:18:54.842 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I could believe that you are Izumi-kun

230
00:18:55.759 --> 00:18:57.719 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
without any doubt.

231
00:19:03.892 --> 00:19:05.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>You stupid girl.</i>

232
00:19:05.269 --> 00:19:07.312 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>You knew this from the start.</i>

233
00:19:11.733 --> 00:19:12.776 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But…</i>

234
00:19:22.077 --> 00:19:24.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Why are you going to
the trouble of seeing her?

235
00:19:24.496 --> 00:19:28.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I can't ignore her when she says
it's the last favor she'll ever ask.

236
00:19:28.500 --> 00:19:30.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I find this incomprehensible.

237
00:19:36.717 --> 00:19:39.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe I'm a little early.

238
00:19:39.261 --> 00:19:40.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shinichi, I sense my kind.

239
00:19:41.722 --> 00:19:44.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not just one but three.

240
00:19:44.308 --> 00:19:45.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, five?

241
00:19:45.517 --> 00:19:47.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How many are there?

242
00:19:47.352 --> 00:19:48.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're that way.

243
00:19:48.812 --> 00:19:53.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>What needs to change</i>
<i>is our individual mentality.</i>

244
00:19:53.817 --> 00:19:55.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Debating global environmental</i>
<i>conservation…</i>

245
00:19:55.777 --> 00:19:58.864 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It appears they are aware of our presence,
but they aren't taking any action.

246
00:19:58.947 --> 00:20:00.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm suddenly realizing

247
00:20:00.824 --> 00:20:04.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that we're kind of like Kitaro
and his dad, from the cartoon.

248
00:20:04.828 --> 00:20:06.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They are approximately 60 meters away.

249
00:20:06.788 --> 00:20:08.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Eight of them total.

250
00:20:08.332 --> 00:20:11.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Two are close to the ground
and six are high up.

251
00:20:11.627 --> 00:20:13.545 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perhaps on a stand of some sort.

252
00:20:14.338 --> 00:20:18.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Would you be willing to forego your cars
in order to prevent polluting the air?

253
00:20:18.342 --> 00:20:20.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is difficult in the extreme
to consider reversing

254
00:20:20.427 --> 00:20:22.179 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the progress we have made
as a civilization.

255
00:20:22.262 --> 00:20:24.348 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
However, if we do not,
at least in some aspects…

256
00:20:24.431 --> 00:20:26.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The six of them up there.
They're all parasites?

257
00:20:26.975 --> 00:20:28.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Two below, too.

258
00:20:28.727 --> 00:20:30.437 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
At this distance,
it is difficult to identify them,

259
00:20:30.520 --> 00:20:33.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but we may be able to
if we make eye contact.

260
00:20:34.483 --> 00:20:35.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh?

261
00:20:42.616 --> 00:20:43.742 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did he see us?

262
00:20:43.825 --> 00:20:45.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But in this crowd…

263
00:20:45.619 --> 00:20:46.912 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He saw us.

264
00:20:46.995 --> 00:20:48.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Our eyes met,

265
00:20:48.622 --> 00:20:51.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but they do not seem
to be very interested in us.

266
00:20:51.583 --> 00:20:53.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now that we've seen a rare sight,

267
00:20:53.418 --> 00:20:54.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
let's get out of here for now.

268
00:20:55.003 --> 00:20:55.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah.

269
00:20:57.756 --> 00:21:00.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>A parasite running for mayor?</i>

270
00:21:00.133 --> 00:21:01.635 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What are they planning?</i>

271
00:21:01.718 --> 00:21:03.011 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh! Izumi!

272
00:21:03.762 --> 00:21:05.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why are you here?

273
00:21:06.014 --> 00:21:07.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why?

274
00:21:07.516 --> 00:21:09.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I live in this neighborhood,

275
00:21:09.851 --> 00:21:11.937 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I'm the one who asked you
to meet me here.

276
00:21:12.020 --> 00:21:13.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh. Right.

277
00:21:14.648 --> 00:21:16.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
…but it is at the municipal level that

278
00:21:17.025 --> 00:21:18.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
environmental issues can be
addressed in a practical sense,

279
00:21:19.069 --> 00:21:21.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
rather than at the national level.

280
00:21:21.863 --> 00:21:23.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>This isn't good.</i>

281
00:22:36.063 --> 00:22:36.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
&lrm;RICH COEXTISTENCE OF PEOPLE AND NATURE

